myapp.data

Class Location

  • java.lang.Object
    • myapp.data.Location
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Location
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Location is a object representing the Location-holders position. This is supposed to belong to for example a Bike or a Docking object.
    See Also:

    • Constructor Detail

      • Location

        public Location(java.lang.String name,
                boolean getCoords)
        This constructor is meant for creating location object where to lat, long and altitude is unknown. By entering the name and setting getCoords to true it will automatically create a complete Location object.
        Parameters:
        name - the address of the location
        getCoords - True = getting coords from google maps, False = not getting coords.

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object o)

        Determines wether this Location equals the Object.

        They are equal if the Object is an instance of a Location and both their latitude and their longitude are equal.

        Overrides:
        equals in class java.lang.Object
        Parameters:
        o - the Object to compare to
        Returns:
        true if they are equal, false otherwise
